Runtime benchmark results

These are the results as boxplots split across FI method with varying \(n\) (n_samples) and \(p\) (n_features).

Runtime (log10 seconds)

Runtime in seconds as measured during experiments on a high performance computing environment are subject to variance due to the shared environment. Measurement is taken for each method exclusively around the function call doing the feature importance computation.

PFI

PFI runtime scaling across packages by number of features, faceted by sample size and number of repeats.

CFI

CFI runtime scaling across packages by number of features using Gaussian sampler, faceted by sample size and number of repeats.

mSAGE

mSAGE runtime scaling with sage_n_samples = 100 and n_permutations = 100, faceted by sample size.

mSAGE runtime scaling with n = 5000 (excluding sage package), faceted by n_permutations and sage_n_samples.

mSAGE runtime scaling with n = 5000 and n_permutations = 100, faceted by sage_n_samples.

cSAGE

cSAGE runtime scaling with sage_n_samples = 100 and n_permutations = 100 using Gaussian sampler, faceted by sample size.

cSAGE runtime scaling with n = 5000 using Gaussian sampler, faceted by n_permutations and sage_n_samples.
